[I] The ISC DNS server, resolver library and utilities

[T] The Berkeley Internet Name Domain (BIND) implements an Internet
[T] name server for Unix operating systems. The BIND consists of a server
[T] (or `daemon') called `named' and a resolver library. A name server is
[T] a network service that enables clients to name resources or objects
[T] and share this information with other objects in the network.

[U] https://www.isc.org/bind/

[A] ISC Software <bind@isc.org>
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/server base/system
[F] CROSS

[E] opt krb5
[E] opt systemtap

[L] Free-to-use
[V] 9.20.22

[CV-URL] https://ftp.isc.org/isc/bind9/
[D] 0b199e8ba32adb78d755355a5c1cdd2db50866801c5ebd9a55efe7c4 bind-9.20.22.tar.xz https://ftp.isc.org/isc/bind9/9.20.22/

